WEBVTT

00:01.609 --> 00:02.998
Stella: Previously on
"Life Sentence"...

00:03.040 --> 00:04.257
Someone should convert
this into a bar.

00:04.300 --> 00:05.346
This is amazing.

00:05.390 --> 00:07.471
You want to buy a bar?

00:07.520 --> 00:08.783
Why do you think a bank

00:08.830 --> 00:10.480
is gonna hand you money
to open a bar?

00:10.530 --> 00:13.044
Because I have a friend
who knows all the ins and outs

00:13.100 --> 00:14.704
on the financial stuff,
and he's gonna coach me.

00:14.750 --> 00:16.354
This is gonna turn out
to be me, isn't it?

00:16.400 --> 00:18.266
Ida: I've been thinking
about our Kiss.

00:18.320 --> 00:19.879
I've been thinking
about that, too.

00:19.930 --> 00:21.750
I think that we both know
that moment is over.

00:21.800 --> 00:24.235
Yeah, that's exactly
what I was thinking.

00:24.280 --> 00:25.406
This could be
something real.

00:25.460 --> 00:27.588
The last real thing I had
I screwed up.

00:27.630 --> 00:29.018
My big brother's name
was Jesse.

00:29.070 --> 00:31.232
And every single patient
I treat, I see him.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.987
When I lose one, I lose
my brother all over again.

00:34.030 --> 00:35.896
You had a wedding with Pippa?!
So, what?

00:35.940 --> 00:38.204
Sh-She just left you
at the altar?

00:38.250 --> 00:39.684
Stella:
I had told myself

00:39.730 --> 00:41.289
that things between me and Wes
were fine after Pippa,

00:41.340 --> 00:42.557
but maybe they're not?

00:42.600 --> 00:43.726
Do you have
feelings for him? No.

00:43.780 --> 00:44.861
We might need
someone to help us

00:44.910 --> 00:46.127
sort through
our specific problems,

00:46.170 --> 00:47.649
like Dr. Grant and Pippa.

00:47.690 --> 00:49.306
Counseling. We do have
a lot to sort through.

00:49.350 --> 00:50.772
So you're our
couples counselor?

00:50.830 --> 00:53.470
Miles: Yes, I assure you,
I am qualified.

00:54.700 --> 00:56.395
Great session.
See you next time.

00:56.440 --> 00:59.228
Actually, we wanted
to talk to you about that.

00:59.270 --> 01:02.797
We've been doing so well
since we started coming here...

01:02.840 --> 01:04.535
We've been "checking in"
night and day,

01:04.580 --> 01:06.093
looking for
"win-win solutions..."

01:06.150 --> 01:08.403
And we are back to having
Sara Bareilles candle sex

01:08.450 --> 01:10.145
like three times a week.

01:11.240 --> 01:13.106
We were just wondering

01:13.160 --> 01:16.107
if maybe it was time
to take off the training wheels.

01:16.160 --> 01:18.857
And work our new tools
all by ourselves.

01:18.900 --> 01:21.688
At home.
Without you there.

01:21.730 --> 01:23.596
Did I do something wrong?

01:23.640 --> 01:26.382
No, not at all!
You did something right.

01:26.430 --> 01:28.467
In fact, congratulations
are in order.

01:28.520 --> 01:30.033
You did it, kid.
Yep.

01:30.090 --> 01:32.559
Well, it sounds like
you made a decision.

01:32.610 --> 01:35.216
And that you made it
together.

01:35.260 --> 01:37.046
So, good for you.

01:37.090 --> 01:40.310
But if anything comes up,
my door is always open.

01:40.360 --> 01:41.703
<i>-0
Oh, My -</i>

01:41.750 --> 01:43.570
Well, actually, no.
Your door is locked.

01:43.620 --> 01:45.395
Ah,
It does that sometimes.

01:48.320 --> 01:49.185
There.

01:49.230 --> 01:50.311
-Oh, okay.
-Bye.

01:50.370 --> 01:52.452
-See ya.
-Bye.

01:52.500 --> 01:54.150
Was that too abrupt?

01:54.200 --> 01:56.237
I mean, maybe we should have
had a few more sessions?

01:56.290 --> 01:59.373
No. We've been at it for weeks,
and it's worked wonders,

01:59.420 --> 02:01.730
but now we need
to try it on our own.

02:01.770 --> 02:03.158
See if it sticks,
you know?

02:03.210 --> 02:04.462
Yeah, but I gotta go.

02:04.510 --> 02:06.239
I've got a volunteer shift
with my name on it.

02:06.300 --> 02:08.371
Yeah, I should probably
get back to work, as well.

02:08.430 --> 02:10.205
Aiden's been texting
about "a surprise”

02:10.259 --> 02:12.206
he has for me,
and I'm terrified.

02:12.260 --> 02:13.557
Oh.
Is everything okay?

02:13.610 --> 02:15.169
We just haven't really been
seeing eye-to-eye

02:15.220 --> 02:17.643
on what things are and are not
worth spending money on.

02:17.700 --> 02:18.917
But I'll sort it out.

02:18.960 --> 02:21.133
I am looking for
"win-win solutions."

02:26.880 --> 02:30.532
Not to brag, but I was really
killing it at marriage.

02:30.580 --> 02:31.661
Well, thank you
for nothing!

02:31.710 --> 02:33.530
And work was going well, too.

02:33.580 --> 02:35.537
Stella, there's something foul
in the break-room fridge.

02:35.590 --> 02:36.921
Can you
get to the bottom of it?

02:36.980 --> 02:38.846
Are we short
on janitors today?

02:38.890 --> 02:40.585
No, why?

02:40.630 --> 02:44.021
NO reason.
I am on it.

02:44.070 --> 02:46.027
Hey, Elaine,
is everything okay?

02:46.070 --> 02:47.765
Sheila in Community Outreach
just quit

02:47.810 --> 02:49.153
and left me
with a half-planned

02:49.210 --> 02:51.110
bone marrow drive
at the rec center.

02:51.170 --> 02:53.593
Why would she plan a bone marrow
drive at the rec center?

02:53.650 --> 02:55.300
18- to 30-year-olds
are the most viable donors,

02:55.340 --> 02:57.513
and nobody under the age of 60
goes to the rec center.

02:57.560 --> 02:58.868
You know a lot
about bone marrow.

02:58.910 --> 02:59.991
I was supposed to
have a transplant,

03:00.040 --> 03:01.257
but we couldn't
find a match.

03:01.310 --> 03:02.914
I ended up
getting into a trial,

03:02.960 --> 03:04.655
but I know that most kids
don't make it that far,

03:04.700 --> 03:06.395
so that's why these drives
are so important.

03:06.440 --> 03:07.965
I could really
use your help.

03:08.010 --> 03:09.614
Sure. What do you need?Take the whole thing over.

03:09.660 --> 03:11.799
Starting with getting a few
hundred 18- to 30-year-olds

03:11.840 --> 03:13.615
to the rec center
on Friday.

03:13.670 --> 03:16.662
Well, that is my demo,
so leave it me.

03:16.710 --> 03:19.054
I-I won't let you down!

03:21.760 --> 03:26.231
So, Gina and I are
kinda getting serious.

03:26.290 --> 03:27.246
Oh? Do tell.

03:27.290 --> 03:29.543
We're talking
about the future.

03:29.600 --> 03:31.284
And, uh, to that end,

03:31.340 --> 03:35.072
I may have told her that you
and I were officially divorced.

03:35.120 --> 03:36.599
Oh.

03:43.440 --> 03:46.307
- Are these
divorce papers?

03:46.350 --> 03:47.784
Sorry to spring this
on you,

03:47.830 --> 03:50.481
but I didn't think
it would be a problem,

03:50.530 --> 03:54.444
given the fact that...
you left me.

03:54.490 --> 03:56.049
No. It's not a problem.

03:56.100 --> 03:57.613
I would be thrilled
to sign these.

03:57.670 --> 03:59.274
Give 'em the old
Jane Hancock.

03:59.320 --> 04:02.881
Make my mark.
I just, um...

04:02.930 --> 04:05.012
You know,
I don't have a pen.

04:07.420 --> 04:08.490
Oh.

04:14.250 --> 04:19.029
You know, uh, signing divorce
papers is like peeing --

04:19.079 --> 04:21.515
hard to do with
someone watching.

04:21.560 --> 04:23.870
Take your time.

04:23.910 --> 04:26.345
And thank you for being
so great about this.

04:26.390 --> 04:27.869
Of course.

04:27.910 --> 04:31.210
Love Gina.
So happy for you.

04:31.270 --> 04:32.396
Thanks.

04:39.230 --> 04:41.483
Don't worry about a thing

04:41.540 --> 04:45.056
You'll learn to live again

04:45.110 --> 04:47.147
You're gonna learn
to live again

04:47.190 --> 04:51.366
Oh, oh, oh

04:54.030 --> 04:55.247
Ta-da!

04:55.290 --> 04:57.759
Uh...
I'm confused.

04:57.810 --> 05:00.290
I thought we agreed you were
gonna take care of the sign.

05:00.340 --> 05:02.468
And I did.
It works perfectly now.

05:02.510 --> 05:04.387
No, no,
I meant take it down

05:04.430 --> 05:07.070
and put up a sign
that says "bar."

05:07.130 --> 05:09.644
But this sign is cool
and vintage and --

05:09.700 --> 05:11.350
Does not say
the word "bar."

05:11.390 --> 05:13.392
"Cause we're not a bar, Wes.
We're a speakeasy.

05:13.440 --> 05:15.260
We don't want just anybody
coming in here.

05:15.310 --> 05:19.099
We want the mystique...
of Miss Steak.

05:19.140 --> 05:22.440
So, what you're saying is,
you spent money on a sign

05:22.490 --> 05:25.619
that keeps our bar a secret
from the general public?

05:25.670 --> 05:27.365
Yeah.
Now you're getting it.

05:27.410 --> 05:28.923
Hey, guys.
What's up?

05:28.980 --> 05:32.063
I just wanted to, uh,
offer my, uh, congratulations.

05:32.110 --> 05:33.714
I had no idea that
you were doing this.

05:33.760 --> 05:35.455
Wait. Really?
No one told you?

05:35.500 --> 05:36.638
Not a soul.

05:36.680 --> 05:38.068
I actually found out
from Lizzie

05:38.120 --> 05:39.451
before she left town
to meet with her publisher.

05:39.510 --> 05:41.672
Anyways, uh, she wanted me
to drop this off.

05:41.730 --> 05:44.552
It's, uh, an old framed
photo of this place.

05:44.600 --> 05:45.772
She figured that
it'd be nice to have

05:45.820 --> 05:47.470
once you guys take down
the old sign.

05:47.520 --> 05:48.908
We're not taking
the sign down.

05:48.950 --> 05:50.679
So, how are people supposed to
know that this is a bar?

05:50.740 --> 05:52.515
Oh! I rest my case.

05:52.560 --> 05:53.641
They're not
supposed to know,

05:53.700 --> 05:57.819
but then they come in
and it is one.

05:57.870 --> 05:59.395
That is cool!
Okay. Okay.

05:59.440 --> 06:00.692
And I rest my case.

06:00.750 --> 06:03.617
Oh! Oh! Oh!

06:03.660 --> 06:05.446
-Whoa!
-I'm gonna get that fixed.

06:05.490 --> 06:06.571
No, you're not!

06:06.620 --> 06:08.440
Come on, Wes.
I know bars.

06:08.490 --> 06:12.529
I know what makes bars cool
because I am the cool one.

06:12.580 --> 06:13.979
I think we're
equally cool.

06:14.020 --> 06:16.842
Really? I think your
flannel shirt is tucked in.

06:16.890 --> 06:18.801
Look, the point is,
we are gonna run out of money

06:18.850 --> 06:21.717
if we keep wasting it
on signs that don't work

06:21.770 --> 06:23.761
and whatever it is
you're about to show me.

06:23.810 --> 06:27.155
Custom-etched glasses with
a graphic of my design.

06:27.210 --> 06:28.632
Goes with the whole
"what people in the '50s

06:28.690 --> 06:30.385
thought the future
would look like" vibe.

06:30.430 --> 06:32.683
You mean the "mid-century
modern" furniture

06:32.740 --> 06:33.901
that you
spent too much on?

06:33.950 --> 06:36.647
Oh! It's super comfy.

06:38.180 --> 06:41.343
Wes, most bars close
within the first three months

06:41.400 --> 06:44.040
"cause people come once
and they don't come back.

06:44.090 --> 06:47.003
I am trying to create a vibe
that creates a buzz

06:47.050 --> 06:48.484
that prevents that
from happening.

06:48.530 --> 06:50.441
And I am trying to make sure
that we don't close

06:50.490 --> 06:52.185
before we even open.

06:52.230 --> 06:54.699
You have already blown through
our four-week start-up fund.

06:54.760 --> 06:56.751
Then we'll open early.
How about Friday?

06:56.800 --> 06:58.017
Diego, are you free Friday?

06:58.060 --> 06:59.585
Sure,
I've got nothing going on.

06:59.630 --> 07:01.678
Because nobody asked me
to be a part of anything.

07:01.720 --> 07:03.233
How are we
gonna open early

07:03.290 --> 07:04.678
when we don't even have
money for advertising?

07:04.720 --> 07:06.597
Can't you move
some numbers around?

07:06.640 --> 07:07.983
There are no numbers
to move.

07:08.030 --> 07:09.941
Then we'll get creative.

07:09.990 --> 07:12.459
All right, you, you put
your thinking cap on,

07:12.510 --> 07:14.729
and I...

07:14.780 --> 07:17.943
will fire up
the snow cone machine.

07:18.000 --> 07:20.435
By the way, I-I bought
a snow cone machine.

07:24.050 --> 07:27.088
-Oh. Dr. Grant, hello.
-Hey.

07:27.140 --> 07:29.700
So, I am hosting this
bone marrow drive on Friday,

07:29.750 --> 07:31.616
and I was wondering if --No.

07:31.660 --> 07:34.095
Well, you didn't hear
what I needed.

07:34.140 --> 07:35.278
Well, you said
it was on Friday,

07:35.320 --> 07:37.015
and I'm not available
on Friday.

07:37.060 --> 07:39.495
Okay. Well, do you think
that I could have access

07:39.540 --> 07:40.848
to your patient profiles

07:40.890 --> 07:42.369
to see if there's
a potential match?

07:42.410 --> 07:44.492
Sure. I will, uh,
leave them here for later.

07:44.550 --> 07:46.279
Hey?

07:46.330 --> 07:47.764
Are you okay?

07:47.810 --> 07:49.585
Yeah.
Why wouldn't I be okay?

07:49.640 --> 07:51.984
I don't know.
That's why I was asking.

07:52.030 --> 07:53.634
Don't worry about me,
Stella.

07:59.390 --> 08:01.347
Oh! Sorry.

08:03.520 --> 08:05.124
Thank you for this.

08:05.180 --> 08:08.081
It's been a weird day, and your
grilled cheese comforts me.

08:08.130 --> 08:12.567
My trick is the Dijon mustard.
It really pops the cheddar.

08:12.620 --> 08:13.837
MmMmm.

08:13.880 --> 08:15.871
I mean,
I'm happy for Peter,

08:15.930 --> 08:19.275
so why am I freaking out
about signing some papers?

08:19.320 --> 08:24.099
Well, because divorce
just seems final, you know.

08:24.150 --> 08:25.458
One day
you're part of something,

08:25.500 --> 08:26.843
and the next day
your brother-in-laws

08:26.890 --> 08:28.756
are opening up a bar
without you.

08:28.810 --> 08:30.938
Does Peter think he's gonna
marry this woman?

08:30.980 --> 08:34.462
Do Wes and Aiden think I'm not
cool enough to be part of it?

08:34.510 --> 08:36.854
I should just take the plunge
and keep moving forward, right?

08:36.900 --> 08:39.335
I should just talk to them.
Just ask them straight up.

08:39.380 --> 08:40.813
You know what I like

08:40.860 --> 08:43.557
I like that we really
listen to each other.

08:43.610 --> 08:45.032
Hmm.

08:45.080 --> 08:46.696
-Hey, babe.
-Hi.

08:46.740 --> 08:47.775
-Yep.

08:47.830 --> 08:49.127
How was your day?

08:49.180 --> 08:50.955
Well, your brother
spent all of our money

08:51.000 --> 08:52.786
and wants the bar
to be a secret.

08:52.830 --> 08:54.559
That does not sound good.

08:54.620 --> 08:55.917
Nope.
How was your day?

08:55.970 --> 08:57.779
It was partly amazing.

08:57.840 --> 09:01.356
I get to run a bone marrow
drive for the hospital.

09:01.410 --> 09:02.832
-Babe, that's great!
-I know.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.961
I might directly
save a life.

09:05.020 --> 09:07.318
Wait. Why is it only
partly amazing?

09:07.370 --> 09:10.624
Well, I have to get
a couple hundred 20-somethings

09:10.680 --> 09:12.193
to show up
at the rec center,

09:12.240 --> 09:13.969
and while I have a decent
advertising budget,

09:14.030 --> 09:16.988
I just don't know how
I'm going to get them there.

09:17.030 --> 09:20.250
<i>I can offer you a very expensive
SNOW cone machine.</i>

09:21.820 --> 09:23.424
Aiden bought
a snow cone machine.

09:23.470 --> 09:24.596
That makes sense.

09:24.650 --> 09:27.290
Snow was always
his favorite food group.

09:27.340 --> 09:29.479
That's not a bad idea,
actually.

09:29.520 --> 09:32.990
What? Luring them
in with something fun.

09:33.050 --> 09:37.169
How about...
a bar opening?

09:37.220 --> 09:38.654
That's kind of perfect.

09:38.700 --> 09:39.747
Look at us.

09:39.790 --> 09:42.703
Yeah.We're doing so well.

09:42.750 --> 09:46.789
We definitely
do not need therapy.

09:46.840 --> 09:48.490
Sorry. What'd you say?

09:56.680 --> 09:57.761
-Ida!
-Hey!

09:57.810 --> 09:58.766
What are you
doing here?

09:58.810 --> 09:59.982
Oh, I just
dropped by to say...

10:00.030 --> 10:02.727
you've been served.

10:02.770 --> 10:04.022
Signed, sealed,
delivered.

10:04.080 --> 10:07.641
I'm...not yours
anymore.

10:07.690 --> 10:08.771
Thank you.

10:08.820 --> 10:10.811
Thank you.

10:10.870 --> 10:12.167
For what?

10:12.220 --> 10:15.690
For 30 years...
and three beautiful children.

10:24.580 --> 10:26.708
See you around,
Mr. Abbott.

10:26.750 --> 10:30.835
See you around,
Mrs...Ida.

10:40.070 --> 10:41.674
Aiden: You know I want
to help you, sis,

10:41.720 --> 10:43.893
but I got to say,
a bone marrow drive --

10:43.940 --> 10:46.022
not exactly a sexy way
to open a place.

10:46.080 --> 10:49.072
But it is a great way to get
a crowd together last-minute

10:49.120 --> 10:50.815
without spending money
that we don't have.

10:50.860 --> 10:53.864
Plus, Aiden, you can
make anything sexy.

10:53.910 --> 10:56.902
You're right.
I can even pull off jorts.

10:56.960 --> 10:58.166
Let's do this.

10:58.220 --> 10:59.699
The more people
we get to come,

10:59.740 --> 11:01.048
the better chance we have
of saving a life.

11:01.090 --> 11:02.694
So we need to hand out
all of these flyers.

11:02.740 --> 11:04.913
Well, can we at least agree
to be selective

11:04.960 --> 11:06.177
about who we
give them out to?

11:06.230 --> 11:08.528
So...basically
just pretty girls?

11:08.580 --> 11:10.617
A few dudes.
Like at a five-to-one ratio.

11:10.670 --> 11:14.447
Okay. Operation Bone Drive/
Bar Alive is a go, people.

11:14.490 --> 11:17.016
Yeah, let's definitely
not call it that.

11:17.060 --> 11:18.494
Yeah, I realized that
the minute I said it.

11:18.540 --> 11:21.100
Come on, Aiden!
You can make this sexy!

11:21.150 --> 11:23.289
Oh, baby,
are you goin' my way

11:23.330 --> 11:25.936
I see you kicking off
for holiday

11:25.980 --> 11:30.759
So maybe get to know you,
baby, don't know you at all

11:30.820 --> 11:32.151
Uh, no, no. Tell me how you know

11:32.210 --> 11:34.907
I'm not crazy or a fiend,
oh, oh

11:34.950 --> 11:37.590
Not, not stalker and obscene

11:37.650 --> 11:41.951
Like, like how
you know what I see, oh, okay

11:42.000 --> 11:44.958
Got a feeling, got a feeling,
got a feeling, got a feeling

11:45.000 --> 11:47.697
Got a feeling, got a feeling,
got a feeling, got a feeling

11:47.750 --> 11:49.559
Got a feeling, got a feeling,
got a feeling

11:49.620 --> 11:51.748
I got a feeling,
I got a feeling, got a feeling

11:51.790 --> 11:53.349
Feeling, feeling,
feeling, feeling

11:53.400 --> 11:55.789
I got, got, got,
to get, get, to get

11:55.840 --> 11:58.753
And take your time
and try not to wreck it

11:58.800 --> 12:01.269
On, on, on, off,
off for all kids

12:01.320 --> 12:04.972
Get, get up
and make up your own dance

12:05.020 --> 12:06.101
Hello.

12:06.160 --> 12:07.810
Hi. We are hosting
a bone marrow drive,

12:07.850 --> 12:09.329
and we would love
for you to come.

12:09.380 --> 12:10.893
You will love it. It will be
the best thing for you.

12:10.940 --> 12:12.192
And there might be
a free drink

12:12.250 --> 12:13.411
if you're one of
the first ones there.

12:13.470 --> 12:15.245
Yes.
And give some to your friends.

12:15.290 --> 12:17.201
Like hanging
on a darkened cloud

12:17.250 --> 12:18.854
The wind is movin' slow

12:18.910 --> 12:19.854
Hey, beautiful.

12:19.910 --> 12:21.071
What's a guy got to do

12:21.130 --> 12:22.643
to get you to give him
a little bone marrow?

12:22.690 --> 12:24.738
Well, that all depends --
Oh, Aiden.

12:24.780 --> 12:25.736
Mom?

12:25.780 --> 12:26.770
Hey, Mom.
What are you doing here?

