Aiden and I both agree
that we do not need her money.

26:18.700 --> 26:20.350
We're gonna find
another way.

26:20.400 --> 26:23.483
All right, then I better
start getting ready, too.

26:23.530 --> 26:25.089
-Okay.
-Bye.

26:25.140 --> 26:27.142
Bye.

26:27.190 --> 26:29.181
-Hey.
-Hey.

26:29.230 --> 26:31.847
Hey, guys?
You, uh, need anything?

26:31.890 --> 26:34.496
Diego, good news!

26:34.540 --> 26:36.679
We just made room
for a new partner,

26:36.720 --> 26:40.065
and naturally, you're the
first person we thought of.

26:40.120 --> 26:42.373
All we need from you is a
small investment, and you're in.

26:42.420 --> 26:44.639
Finally!
Ah, come here!

26:44.690 --> 26:47.682
Oh!
I have been waiting

26:47.730 --> 26:49.209
for you guys to ask me
to be your partner!

26:49.250 --> 26:50.991
-Thank you!

26:51.040 --> 26:52.690
No. No. I can't do it.

26:52.740 --> 26:54.037
Wait, really?

26:54.090 --> 26:55.649
You just said you wanted
to be a partner.

26:55.700 --> 26:58.783
I wanted you to wantme
to be your partner.

26:58.830 --> 27:01.003
But I got kids
and a mortgage and --

27:01.050 --> 27:03.394
'Nough said.
I'll find someone else.

27:03.440 --> 27:06.705
Quick thought.
Uh, if I were your partner,

27:06.750 --> 27:10.709
I actually would spring
for a bar sign out front.

27:10.750 --> 27:12.058
I mean, how are people
gonna come in

27:12.100 --> 27:13.499
if they can't find
the place, right?

27:15.190 --> 27:17.887
Fine! Geez.
I'll put out a sign.

27:28.860 --> 27:32.205
Guys, there's a line
around the block!

27:33.950 --> 27:35.907
That's amazing!

27:35.950 --> 27:37.600
Very impressive,
gang.

27:37.650 --> 27:39.698
Let's do this,
shall we?

27:39.740 --> 27:41.344
Ooh, ooh, ooh

27:41.390 --> 27:43.654
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

27:43.700 --> 27:45.828
I see the way that you've
been looking at me

27:45.880 --> 27:49.225
You know that I got
what you wanted

27:49.270 --> 27:51.136
Think I gotta
let you know that we

27:51.190 --> 27:54.535
Were over the day
that we started

27:54.580 --> 27:56.571
It was coming on eventually

27:56.630 --> 27:59.531
The writing was on the wall

27:59.590 --> 28:05.711
And as soon as you move on

28:05.770 --> 28:07.898
We tried to dance

28:07.940 --> 28:10.898
And you didn't
wanna look uncool

28:10.950 --> 28:14.079
You took my hand, and I

28:14.120 --> 28:15.906
Put my trust in you

28:15.950 --> 28:18.078
Hi. Sign up for
the bone marrow registry?I don't think so.

28:18.130 --> 28:19.780
If you're a match,
you could save a life.

28:19.820 --> 28:20.867
Sorry.

28:20.910 --> 28:22.821
Thanks
for your compassion.

28:22.870 --> 28:25.180
Hey, Aiden?!

28:25.220 --> 28:26.437
This guy wants to take
our picture

28:26.480 --> 28:28.300
for the hospital
newsletter.

28:28.350 --> 28:29.397
Great place.

28:29.440 --> 28:30.657
I bet it catches on
like wildfire.

28:30.700 --> 28:32.839
We certainly hope so,
'cause if not...

28:32.880 --> 28:36.874
Hey, how are my
maybe

28:37.490 --> 28:38.798
Can I have a photo
of you three?

28:38.840 --> 28:40.797
Oh, no, she's not
our partner. At all.

28:40.840 --> 28:43.150
Well, she's still improving
the shot considerably.

28:43.190 --> 28:44.624
Sorry, darling,

28:44.670 --> 28:46.934
but you know
this is my good side.

28:48.200 --> 28:51.067
We had to reshoot
our engagement photos.

28:54.640 --> 28:56.984
I also do baby photos,
if you guys are in the market.

28:57.030 --> 29:01.945
Oh, no. Uh, I'm not his wife...
almost once, but not quite.

29:02.000 --> 29:04.298
That's his wife.
Stella?!

29:04.350 --> 29:05.511
Hmm?

29:07.610 --> 29:08.509
-Hi.
-Hi.

29:08.570 --> 29:10.561
-Nice to meet you.
-Yeah.

29:10.610 --> 29:11.827
Smile.

29:14.440 --> 29:16.169
Pippa, may I borrow you
for a moment?

29:16.230 --> 29:19.530
Yeah. Absolutely, Stella.
Anything for you.

29:21.710 --> 29:22.620
What can I do for you?

29:22.670 --> 29:23.922
For starters,
you can tell me

29:23.970 --> 29:25.711
what it is you're really
doing in Asheville.

29:25.760 --> 29:28.104
I'm sorry.
I'm not sure I understand.

29:28.150 --> 29:29.936
It's a simple question,
Pippa.

29:29.980 --> 29:31.493
Why are you here?

29:31.550 --> 29:33.154
Wes needed somebody
to help him,

29:33.200 --> 29:35.191
and I wanted to offer
to be that somebody.

29:35.250 --> 29:37.332
Look, if we're being
perfectly honest,

29:37.380 --> 29:38.859
the both of us know
that the real reason

29:38.900 --> 29:40.595
why you want to
invest in this bar

29:40.640 --> 29:43.860
is so that Wes will be back
in your life in a big way.

29:43.910 --> 29:47.164
I'm here because I want to help
a man I care deeply about.

29:47.220 --> 29:49.029
No. You can't do that.

29:49.090 --> 29:51.252
-Care. Deeply.

29:51.310 --> 29:53.916
I'm sorry, Stella,
but I already do.

29:53.960 --> 29:56.691
Wes and I grew up together.
He's practically family.

29:56.750 --> 29:59.788
And if I can help him,
I have to try.

29:59.840 --> 30:01.797
Or would you rather
I let him fail?

30:01.840 --> 30:03.660
Of course not.

30:03.710 --> 30:07.408
But you have to understand
you are not Wes' somebody.

30:07.450 --> 30:09.009
I am.

30:09.060 --> 30:12.018
Okay, and in a marriage, there's
only room for one somebody.

30:12.070 --> 30:14.414
Stella, hey.
Sorry for interrupting.

30:14.460 --> 30:16.633
Hi. I didn't know
you were gonna make it.

30:16.680 --> 30:20.799
Um, this is Pippa.
Wes' ex.

30:20.860 --> 30:22.077
Nice to meet you.

30:22.120 --> 30:23.076
Will Grant.

30:23.120 --> 30:25.031
Dr. Will Grant?

30:25.080 --> 30:26.070
That's right.

30:26.120 --> 30:29.340
I've heard
all about you.

30:29.390 --> 30:31.427
I'll let you two chat.

30:31.480 --> 30:33.209
-Pleasure.
-Pleasure.

30:33.260 --> 30:34.955
And that's when I realized,

30:35.000 --> 30:38.300
Pippa didn't need to work
her way into our marriage.

30:41.100 --> 30:43.489
Wes had already let her in.

30:43.530 --> 30:45.487
Sorry.
Will you excuse me?

30:47.140 --> 30:48.744
Yeah.

30:54.940 --> 30:56.544
Sorry,
but it's 21 and over.

30:56.590 --> 30:59.548
-I'm 24.
-Sure you are.

30:59.590 --> 31:01.149
Miles! Hi.

31:01.200 --> 31:03.635
Oh, this is our
couples counselor.

31:03.680 --> 31:05.990
I didn't know you were
still in couples therapy.

31:06.030 --> 31:07.589
They're not anymore.

31:07.640 --> 31:09.904
They keep quitting every time
they have a good session.

31:09.950 --> 31:12.032
Okay.
Well, uh, Miles,

31:12.080 --> 31:14.469
would you like to sign up
for the bone marrow registry?

31:14.520 --> 31:16.864
-Great.

31:22.570 --> 31:23.696
Peter!

31:24.530 --> 31:25.964
-Hey!
-This place is great!

31:26.010 --> 31:27.569
I know, right?
Here.

31:27.620 --> 31:29.133
I need to talk to you
about Ida.

31:29.190 --> 31:30.487
Is everything all right?

31:30.540 --> 31:32.053
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
She's fine.

31:32.100 --> 31:33.317
Uh, except that she wants
to go back to college

31:33.360 --> 31:35.101
and she can't afford it.

31:35.150 --> 31:38.142
I was thinking maybe you knew of
scholarships or financial aid.

31:38.200 --> 31:40.237
Why didn't she come
to me with this?

31:40.280 --> 31:41.896
I think she's
a little embarrassed.

31:41.940 --> 31:43.544
She left you to be
her own person.

31:43.590 --> 31:45.069
And now
she needs your help.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.987
And I can't imagine it feels
too good to know that.

31:52.430 --> 31:53.682
Hmm.

31:53.730 --> 31:55.812
You really don't have to
feel bad about the fact

31:55.870 --> 31:57.861
that this is harder than
you thought it would be.

31:57.910 --> 32:00.607
I just thought we were past all
these ridiculous trust issues.

32:00.650 --> 32:02.379
And what am I
still so afraid of?

32:02.440 --> 32:04.044
Maybe what scares you...

32:04.090 --> 32:08.049
is the thought that Wes could
feel the same way about Pippa

32:08.100 --> 32:09.784
that you feel
about Dr. Grant.

32:09.840 --> 32:13.003
I don't have those
feelings for Dr. Grant.

32:13.060 --> 32:14.095
Okay.

32:26.160 --> 32:28.936
Quick announcement.

32:28.990 --> 32:30.242
Girls drink free!

32:32.030 --> 32:36.069
...ly. Girls drink freely.
But also drink responsibly.

32:36.120 --> 32:37.849
And please pay for stuff.

32:40.610 --> 32:43.170
Peter.
Hi! Wow!

32:43.220 --> 32:44.301
You look handsome.

32:44.350 --> 32:46.864
Ida, you look...20.

32:46.920 --> 32:49.002
I could mistake you
for just another coed.

32:49.050 --> 32:50.563
Like father, like son.

32:50.620 --> 32:52.918
There's just something
about being around them.

32:52.970 --> 32:55.837
It makes me feel like
I never left school.

32:55.880 --> 32:57.439
Then you should go back.

32:57.490 --> 32:58.707
Oh, yeah, I already
looked into it.

32:58.750 --> 33:00.058
Unfortunately,
I can't afford it.

33:00.100 --> 33:01.443
You can.

33:01.500 --> 33:04.663
Turns out, as the wife
of a college professor,

33:04.720 --> 33:07.234
you can attend the
university tuition-free.

33:07.280 --> 33:09.021
Really?
But wait a minute.

33:09.070 --> 33:11.630
Wait, wait. We're divorced.
You just filed the paperwork.

33:11.680 --> 33:14.024
I haven't.
Not yet.

33:14.070 --> 33:17.119
And I won't, if you
really want to do this.

33:17.160 --> 33:18.241
Well, what about Gina?

33:18.300 --> 33:19.722
I thought
this was important to her.

33:19.780 --> 33:20.906
It is.

33:20.950 --> 33:24.511
But your happiness
is important to me.

33:24.560 --> 33:27.951
And if Gina really is the woman
for me, she'll understand.

33:28.000 --> 33:31.220
You've supported me
through 30 years of marriage.

33:31.270 --> 33:34.080
<i>- _Theleast1lcan do
is give you a few semesters.</i>

33:36.530 --> 33:38.874
Is that
a habanero martini?

33:38.920 --> 33:40.092
Yes.

33:40.140 --> 33:41.665
But I liked these
way before I met you.

33:41.710 --> 33:43.883
Hmm. I thought we weren't
gonna lie to each other.

33:43.930 --> 33:46.979
Right. Oh, I'm -- I'm sorry
I ran off earlier.

33:47.020 --> 33:48.328
How was the dedication?

33:48.370 --> 33:51.237
Ah. It was like
a slow-motion train wreck.

33:51.290 --> 33:52.849
Oh, no. Seriously?
Yeah.

33:52.900 --> 33:55.289
But based on some good advice
that I got earlier,

33:55.330 --> 33:58.152
I decided to forget
about my insane family

33:58.210 --> 34:01.248
and focus on the kid
who got the scholarship.

34:01.300 --> 34:04.338
I'm glad I went.
Thank you.

34:04.390 --> 34:06.074
That was all
Jesse's advice.

34:06.130 --> 34:11.387
No, Stella, I needed somebody,
and you were there for me, so...

34:13.920 --> 34:15.649
-Thank you for coming.
-Yeah.

34:15.699 --> 34:17.485
Yeah. And thank you
for your DNA.

34:17.530 --> 34:18.952
Mmm.
Please don't clone me.

34:19.010 --> 34:21.445
I'm pretty sure one of you
is more than enough.

34:23.190 --> 34:25.147
So the turnout's
amazing.

34:25.190 --> 34:27.147
Yeah, there's a lot
of people here,

34:27.190 --> 34:28.965
but turns out
that 20-somethings

34:29.020 --> 34:30.748
would rather
drink themselves blind

34:30.800 --> 34:33.143
than sign up for a potentially
invasive medical procedure.

34:33.199 --> 34:34.975
And this is news to you?

34:35.020 --> 34:37.239
In fairness, I haven't
had much experience

34:37.290 --> 34:39.327
being a typical
20-something.

34:39.380 --> 34:41.109
So how many more
donors do you need?

34:41.159 --> 34:42.672
A lot.

34:53.520 --> 34:57.525
Um, hey, how cool
is this place, right?

35:00.570 --> 35:02.698
-I don't know.

35:02.750 --> 35:04.002
But if he starts singing,

35:04.050 --> 35:05.870
I'm gonna burn
this bar to the ground.

35:05.920 --> 35:08.230
Does anyone out here drink gin?
Huh

35:08.280 --> 35:10.271
There they are!
There's my people!

35:10.320 --> 35:13.711
So, I, uh --
I started drinking gin, um,

35:13.760 --> 35:16.536
because my older brother, Jesse,
he -- he told me that --

35:16.590 --> 35:18.718
that James Bond was
the coolest guy ever.

35:18.760 --> 35:20.319
And I-I thought
that my older brother

35:20.370 --> 35:24.546
was the coolest guy ever,
so, well...here I am.

35:28.950 --> 35:31.988
Drinking gin alone.

35:32.040 --> 35:35.556
I would give anything if --
if Jesse was here tonight.

35:35.610 --> 35:39.433
He would love this place.
He would.

35:39.480 --> 35:41.790
But he's not here.

35:41.830 --> 35:47.394
Because he -- he died three
weeks before his 21st birthday.

35:48.450 --> 35:50.396
Um...

35:52.360 --> 35:55.239
He had cancer, and he --

35:55.280 --> 35:58.409
he needed
a bone marrow transplant,

35:58.460 --> 36:00.235
and I-I'll never forget
the day that I-I went

36:00.280 --> 36:03.102
to get tested to see
if I was a match.

36:06.030 --> 36:10.979
But I wasn't a match and, uh --
and I couldn't save his life.

36:11.030 --> 36:14.989
But -- But maybe someone
in this room could have.

36:15.040 --> 36:18.340
So if you haven't
gotten swabbed yet,

36:18.390 --> 36:23.783
please...be the hero
that I know you can be.

36:23.830 --> 36:25.127
And if you don't want to do it

36:25.180 --> 36:27.649
for some guy up here
drinking gin,

36:27.700 --> 36:31.876
then -- then do it
for my brother.

36:31.920 --> 36:33.354
Thank you guys.
Cheers!

36:41.370 --> 36:43.020
That was some speech.

36:44.240 --> 36:46.891
I guess Dr. Grant's
still in the picture.

36:46.940 --> 36:48.453
He's not.

36:48.510 --> 36:51.150
And I should never have talked
to you about that whole thing.

36:51.200 --> 36:54.022
You don't want to take my money.
I get that.

36:54.080 --> 36:57.300
But it's me. _
You can always tell me anything.

36:57.340 --> 37:01.470
No, Pip, I can't.
Not anymore.

37:14.360 --> 37:16.351
Will!

37:16.400 --> 37:18.744
Will?!

37:18.800 --> 37:20.666
Hey.

37:20.710 --> 37:22.929
That was some speech.

37:22.970 --> 37:26.326
I really thought I could
keep it together, but...

37:28.460 --> 37:30.451
I'm a mess today.

37:30.500 --> 37:33.288
Well, thank you.

37:33.330 --> 37:36.379
And just so you know,
you are a hero...

37:36.420 --> 37:42.075
to that kid you helped today, to
the kids you help every day...

37:42.120 --> 37:43.463
to me.

37:44.910 --> 37:50.952
And if you miss your brother,
it's okay to be a mess.

37:51.000 --> 37:52.343
It's okay.

37:52.400 --> 37:54.346
It's just a little white lie

37:54.400 --> 37:58.041
If it is all the same to me

37:58.100 --> 38:00.523
And it's just
a little white lie

38:00.580 --> 38:04.539
If I was to blame you

38:06.190 --> 38:08.101
Would you...

38:08.150 --> 38:09.140
What was that?

38:12.110 --> 38:13.418
What was that?

38:13.460 --> 38:16.100
I...I don't --
I don't know.

38:16.160 --> 38:17.889
I-I didn't mean it
to happen that way.

38:17.940 --> 38:21.114
So you did
want it to happen?

38:21.160 --> 38:24.460
Yeah. Of course I wanted it
to happen, but...not now.

38:24.510 --> 38:26.854
No. Not ever.

38:26.910 --> 38:29.299
What?I'm serious. I mean it.

38:30.430 --> 38:34.048
Okay, I'm gonna...
I'm gonna go home now.

38:42.620 --> 38:45.009
Wes! There he is!
We need to celebrate!

38:45.060 --> 38:48.360
Let me watch you do
a couple...shots.

38:48.410 --> 38:49.889
Hey. Are you okay?

38:49.930 --> 38:52.149
I promise I'll figure out
the money stuff.

38:52.190 --> 38:55.490
But tonight, we just
got to enjoy this.

38:55.550 --> 38:58.770
Sorry.
I got to get out of here.

39:00.640 --> 39:02.244
What

39:11.170 --> 39:13.036
Can't believe
the kid who framed

39:13.080 --> 39:15.560
his Least Likely to Succeed
award

39:15.610 --> 39:16.953
is a business owner.

39:17.000 --> 39:19.469
And, by the way, everything
that Aiden is doing

39:19.530 --> 39:21.259
is because of you.

39:21.310 --> 39:24.223
It's because of us.

39:24.270 --> 39:25.442
To us.

39:27.140 --> 39:29.097
[ Mid-tempo music plays,
indistinct singing]

39:30.670 --> 39:32.365
You remember this?

39:32.410 --> 39:35.311
This is the first song
that we ever danced to.

39:35.370 --> 39:38.010
At that sorority mixer
you made me go to.

39:38.070 --> 39:39.799
Yes.

39:39.850 --> 39:42.717
You really missed out
not being bi in college.

39:42.770 --> 39:44.374
No, I didn't.

39:46.600 --> 39:49.240
It's been 100 years since
the last time I asked you this,

39:49.290 --> 39:54.512
but, Ida Kaminsky,
would you like to dance with me?

39:54.560 --> 39:56.119
I'd love to.

40:13.230 --> 40:16.097
Elaine. Hi.
Have you seen my husband?

40:16.150 --> 40:19.586
No, but I have signed up a lot
of people for the registry.

40:19.630 --> 40:21.587
You did a great job.

40:21.630 --> 40:24.850
You make people care, Stella.
It's a strength.

40:24.900 --> 40:26.846
Why does it feel
like a weakness?

40:26.900 --> 40:28.504
-Nothing.

40:28.550 --> 40:31.941
I'm sorry. I just --
I need to find Wes.

40:34.210 --> 40:35.518
Wes, would you
please stop walking?

40:35.560 --> 40:37.517
Would you please
stop following me?

40:37.560 --> 40:39.517
I'm worried about you.
What's going on?

40:39.560 --> 40:41.289
Wes?

40:46.740 --> 40:49.823
Well, I'm thinking
to myself again

40:49.880 --> 40:52.656
Am I always on
the losing end?

40:52.710 --> 40:55.532
You never called back,
you never called back

40:55.580 --> 40:58.572
Well, that's okay, 'cause
I don't talk like that

40:58.630 --> 41:01.884
Wes? Now, I'm waiting
for my time to come

41:01.930 --> 41:04.581
And I know
I'm not the only one

41:04.630 --> 41:07.804
I'll never hold back,
I'll never hold back

41:07.850 --> 41:10.581
Hey, it's me again.
I'm just checking in.

41:10.640 --> 41:12.119
I-I lost track
of you at the bar

41:12.160 --> 41:13.935
and I'm really starting
to get worried,

41:13.990 --> 41:17.506
so just call me back, okay?

41:17.560 --> 41:20.257
"Cause I know
it would be good for you

41:20.300 --> 41:22.644
Talk to me. You don't know,
then I'll show you

41:22.690 --> 41:25.864
Let me show you how

41:25.910 --> 41:28.436
Will you show me how

41:28.480 --> 41:30.790
So meet me in the middle
sometime
